# ERD — FORA multi-tenant runtime

The diagram below is the source of truth for the runtime's data model at v1 GA. Conventions:

- **Every user table** carries the soft-delete + audit columns from ADR-0001: `id uuid PK`, `tenant_id uuid NOT NULL` (RLS column), `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `deleted_at`, `deleted_by`. The diagram lists the table-specific columns; the soft-delete columns are implied.
- **RLS** is enforced on every user table by `tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid` (ADR-0003). The `migrator` and `audit_reader` roles are the only `BYPASSRLS` holders.
- **Cardinality** is drawn in Mermaid `erDiagram` notation. `||--o{` = one-to-many; `||--||` = one-to-one; `}o--o{` = many-to-many via a join table.
- **Forward-only migrations** (architecture memory §6) live in `packages/db-migrator/migrations/`. The four v1 migrations are referenced inline.

## Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram

  %% ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  %% Identity & tenancy
  %% ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  tenants {
    uuid id PK
    text name
    text slug
    text status "active | suspended | offboarded"
    text plan "free | design_partner | ga"
    jsonb settings
  }
  users {
    uuid id PK
    text email
    text display_name
    text status "active | invited | offboarded"
    text mfa_method "webauthn | totp | none"
  }
  tenant_memberships {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    uuid user_id FK
    text role "pm | engineer | qa | security | devops | docs | cto | ceo | board"
    jsonb scopes
  }
  tenant_idp_configs {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    text provider "okta | azure_ad | google | onelogin | generic_oidc"
    text issuer
    text client_id
    text webhook_secret_ref "AWS SM ARN, never inline"
    int webhook_secret_revision
  }
  tenant_webhook_secrets {
    uuid tenant_id FK
    text secret_ref
    bytea hmac_key "KMS-wrapped; never logged"
  }
  agent_identities {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    text agent_name "ba | architect | developer | qa | security | devops | docs | cost | audit | memory"
    text jwt_kid
    timestamptz expires_at
    jsonb allow_list
  }

  %% ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  %% Run lifecycle
  %% ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  agent_runs {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    text status "created | running | waiting_approval | paused | aborted | finished | done"
    text current_stage "ideation | architect | dev | qa | security | devops | docs | done"
    uuid goal_id
    uuid project_id
    text trigger_kind "user | slack | email | schedule | webhook"
    text trigger_actor
    timestamptz started_at
    timestamptz finished_at
    text idempotency_key
    jsonb cost_estimate "tokens_in, tokens_out, usd"
    jsonb cost_actual
  }
  agent_run_stages {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    uuid run_id FK
    text stage "ideation | architect | dev | qa | security | devops | docs"
    text status "pending | running | waiting_approval | approved | rejected | returned | skipped"
    text model_provider "anthropic | openai | failover"
    jsonb inputs
    jsonb outputs
    text artefact_ref
    timestamptz started_at
    timestamptz finished_at
  }
  agent_run_events {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    uuid run_id FK
    text stage
    text event_type "run.created | run.advanced | gate.passed | gate.rejected | ..."
    jsonb payload
    text trace_id
    text idempotency_key
  }
  agent_run_idempotency_keys {
    text key
    uuid tenant_id FK
    uuid run_id FK "nullable until run created"
    text request_fingerprint "SHA-256 hex"
    int response_status
    jsonb response_body
    timestamptz created_at
  }
  agent_run_approvals {
    uuid id PK
    uuid tenant_id FK
    uuid run_id FK
    text stage "nullable for launch gate"
    text gate_kind "ideation->architect | ... | launch"
    text required_role
    text status "pending | approved | rejected | expired"
    text paperclip_interaction_id
    jsonb artefact_refs
    text reason
