## 3. Soft-delete invariant (ADR-0001)

Every user table above carries `deleted_at` and `deleted_by`. The default read path is `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL`. `hard_delete` is a DBA action via the `audit_reader` role and a runbook; it never appears in app code.

## 4. RLS policy shape (ADR-0003)

```sql
CREATE POLICY tenant_isolation ON <table>
  FOR ALL TO runtime_pool
  USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid)
  WITH CHECK (tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid);
```

`packages/db-pool` sets `app.tenant_id` on every checkout. A missing `SET LOCAL` is a tenant leak; the `tenancy-lint` red fixture (`packages/tenancy-lint/test/fixtures/red-no-rls.sql`) catches it in CI.

## 5. Forward-only migration policy

Per architecture memory §6: every migration in `packages/db-migrator/migrations/` is forward-only. Rollback is documented as a comment in the migration file (e.g., `0002` lists the inverse `DROP` operations but does not execute them). Destructive operations are a DBA action with 1Password-held credentials and an audit row.

